# Appliance Tracker - Full Stack Web Application

A full stack web application for tracking appliances, built with **React**, **Node.js/Express**, and **MySQL**. Optional deployment can be done on **AWS** (S3, CloudFront, Elastic Beanstalk, or RDS).

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Technologies Used

- **Frontend:** React, HTML, CSS  
- **Backend:** Node.js, Express.js, RESTful API  
- **Database:** MySQL  
- **Deployment (Optional):** AWS S3, CloudFront, Elastic Beanstalk, RDS  
- **Other Tools:** Axios / Fetch, Git

---

## üìå Project Overview

The Appliance Tracker allows users to:

- Add new appliances with details (name, brand, price, status)  
- View a list of all appliances  
- Update or delete existing appliances  
- Interact with a **REST API** to communicate between frontend and backend  
- Optional: User authentication with JWT  
- Optional: Hosted on AWS for production-ready deployment  

This project demonstrates **full stack development**, **frontend-backend integration**, **database management**, and **cloud deployment**.

